cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.LO, cs.RO, cs.SY

This paper deals with conflict resolution in traffic scenarios, which involves decision-making and coordination among multiple agents. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-categories. The paper also presents a logical framework that adopts concepts from epistemic and modal logic, justification and temporal logic, indicating that it may also belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses how conflict resolution can be done when a vehicle has local, incomplete information, vehicle to vehicle communication (V2V) and partially ordered goals, which suggests that it may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
